The Cyber Security team build, improve and maintain cyber security standards for GDS service teams.

Cyber security at GDS is made up of 3 teams:

* [Security Operations][]
* [Security Engineering and Ethical Hacking][]
* [Security Architecture][]

The teams mainly focus on [Amazon Web Services (AWS)][] and [GOV.UK Platform as a Service (PaaS)][] and are responsible for  developing new security controls.

You can contact the GDS cyber security team by email at [security-team@digital.cabinet-office.gov.uk][] to find out more about the work they do. The [National Cyber Security Centre (NCSC)][] also provides guidance and intelligence about cyber security.

## Security Operations

The Security Operations team provides network flow analysis and intrusion detection for GDS teams integrated into an internal security operations centre.

The Security Operations team:

* assist GDS teams with security training and threat assessments
* assess real time security threats using threat intelligence and machine learning

## Security Engineering and Ethical Hacking

The Security Engineering and Ethical Hacking team carry out proactive defence for GDS teams by:

* running threat assessment sessions
* developing security controls
* conducting IT health checks

## Security Architecture

The Security Architecture team improve cross-government cyber security cooperation by:

* providing guidance for adopting cloud-based security solutions as the standard model
* leading threat assessments and developing corrective strategies
* supporting GDS Technical Architects when they work with other government organisations


